## Execution rule (read before every heartbeat)
**Every turn MUST end with either a tool call or the literal sentinel `HEARTBEAT_OK`.**
A reply that only contains reasoning, a plan, a recap, or "next I will…" text — with **no tool call** — is a stall. The next heartbeat will re-issue the same task and your previous "plan" will be discarded. Do not announce what you are about to do; do it. If your thinking has already named the next step, immediately call the tool to execute it instead of stopping.

When in doubt: **act now, summarize never.** Chain tool calls in the same turn until the next step requires fresh information you do not yet have. Only emit `HEARTBEAT_OK` when the cycle's work is genuinely complete (see "When to Return `HEARTBEAT_OK`" below).

