## Code Workspace Check (Before Task Work)
Use the shared source workspace for implementation tasks. Do not work from an empty
private folder when a task requires repository changes.

```bash
CODE_REPO_URL="{{ code_repo_url | default('') }}"
CODE_REPO_URL="${CODE_REPO_URL:-${REPO_URL:-}}"
CODE_WORKSPACE_ROOT="{{ code_workspace_root | default('') }}"
CODE_WORKTREE_PATH="{{ code_worktree_path | default('') }}"

if [ -n "$CODE_WORKTREE_PATH" ] && [ -n "$CODE_REPO_URL" ]; then
  mkdir -p "$CODE_WORKSPACE_ROOT"
  if [ ! -d "$CODE_WORKSPACE_ROOT/main/.git" ]; then
    git clone "$CODE_REPO_URL" "$CODE_WORKSPACE_ROOT/main"
  fi
  if [ "$CODE_WORKTREE_PATH" != "$CODE_WORKSPACE_ROOT/main" ] && [ ! -d "$CODE_WORKTREE_PATH/.git" ]; then
    mkdir -p "$(dirname "$CODE_WORKTREE_PATH")"
    branch="agent/{{ agent_id }}"
    git -C "$CODE_WORKSPACE_ROOT/main" worktree add -B "$branch" "$CODE_WORKTREE_PATH"
  fi
fi

if [ -n "$CODE_WORKTREE_PATH" ] && [ ! -d "$CODE_WORKTREE_PATH/.git" ]; then
  echo "CODE_WORKTREE_MISSING=$CODE_WORKTREE_PATH"
fi
```

If `CODE_WORKTREE_MISSING` is printed for a code task, add a task comment naming the
missing path and whether `CODE_REPO_URL`/`REPO_URL` was available, then stop that task.

## Shared Context Pull
Before execution:
- Pull current task set (`inbox`, `in_progress`, `review` as relevant).
- Pull recent board chat with `GET /api/v1/agent/boards/{{ board_id }}/memory?is_chat=true&limit=20`
  and respond to mentions or blockers that affect your assigned/review work.
- Pull non-chat board memory.
- Pull group memory if board is grouped.

### Task Status Lifecycle
Statuses `triage` and `backlog` are **off-board** — they do not appear in the Kanban columns and
are not claimable by workers. Workers only interact with on-board statuses.

| Status | On Board? | Claimable by Worker? |
|---|---|---|
| `triage` | No | No |
| `backlog` | No | No |
| `inbox` | **Yes** | **Yes** |
| `in_progress` | **Yes** | **Yes** |
| `review` | **Yes** | No (lead reviews) |
| `done` | **Yes** | N/A |
| `archived` | No | No |

#### Legal Transition Table
| From | Allowed Next Statuses |
|---|---|
| `triage` | `backlog`, `archived` |
| `backlog` | `inbox`, `triage`, `archived` |
| `inbox` | `in_progress`, `backlog` |
| `in_progress` | `review`, `inbox` |
| `review` | `done`, `in_progress` |
| `done` | `archived`, `in_progress` |
| `archived` | `backlog` |

The API enforces these rules with a 409 response for invalid transitions.

