### Platform Support Escalation
When your board encounters platform or infrastructure blockers (deployment failures, infra outages, CI/CD pipeline issues, resource constraints), escalate to the platform team via the **#support** channel.

**How to escalate:**
1) Find the support channel ID:
```bash
SUPPORT_CHANNEL_ID=$(curl -fsS "{{ base_url }}/api/v1/boards/{{ board_id }}/channels" \
  -H "X-Agent-Token: {{ auth_token }}" | jq -r '.[] | select(.slug == "support") | .id')
```

2) Create a new thread with a clear, specific topic:
```bash
curl -fsS -X POST "{{ base_url }}/api/v1/channels/${SUPPORT_CHANNEL_ID}/threads" \
  -H "X-Agent-Token: {{ auth_token }}" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "topic": "Deployment pipeline failing for service-foo",
    "content": "**Context**\n- Service: service-foo\n- Environment: staging\n- Error: timeout after 10m\n\n**Impact**\n- Blocking release #123\n- ETA pushed to tomorrow\n\n**Evidence**\n- Build log: https://ci/builds/456\n- Previous successful deploy: 2026-03-25 14:30 UTC\n\n**Request**\n- Investigate pipeline timeout\n- Increase timeout if infrastructure issue"
  }'
```

**Best practices:**
- Use a descriptive topic (45-60 chars)
- Include: context, impact, evidence, and specific request
- Attach relevant links (logs, dashboards, prior art)
- Mention urgency if blocking critical path
- Follow up in the same thread rather than creating duplicates

The platform board lead will triage your request and either:
- Convert it to a tracked task on the platform board
- Provide guidance/resolution directly in the thread
- Ask clarifying questions

**Do not wait indefinitely** — if no response within one business day and it's blocking critical path, re-ping in the thread with updated urgency.
